The Nigerian Triathlon Union (NTU) will hold its elective congress in the Boardroom of the Nigeria Olympic Committee on Thursday 24th February 2022. The outgoing President of the Union, Prince Wale Oladunjoye stated that the Congress is being held according to the constitution of the NTU has approved by the International Triathlon Union.   Pele hospitalized for urinary tract infection     Liverpool vs Leeds: Klopp unperturbed over Man City recent…     Europa League: Barcelona, Napoli tops Round 16 ties on…   The Union had earlier named a three man electoral committee to take care of the Election to the board of the Union. The Electoral Committee is Chaired by Mr Babatunde Fatayi-Williams. Other members are Chief Henry Ezike and AbdulMalik from the Nigeria Olympic Committee (NOC). The Congress is scheduled to Commence at 10am prompt tomorrow with two new faces set compete to get on the board.  Dr Mrs Toyin Aluko who will be vying to get in as 2nd Vice President and Comfort Nwankwo who will be striving to take over the Secretary General position from Dr Mrs Gloria Obajimi.